WEBVTT

00:03.540 --> 00:04.510
Good evening.

00:04.540 --> 00:07.540
I'm your guest lecturer,
Dr. Sheldon Cooper.

00:12.860 --> 00:16.500
I was expecting applause,

00:16.500 --> 00:20.290
but I suppose stunned silence
is equally appropriate.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.950
I agreed to speak
to you this evening,

00:22.950 --> 00:26.120
because I was told that you're
the best and the brightest

00:26.120 --> 00:28.360
of this university's
doctoral candidates.

00:28.360 --> 00:30.340
Hmm. Of course,
that's like saying

00:30.350 --> 00:33.650
you are the most important
electron in a hydrogen atom.

00:38.320 --> 00:39.070
'Cause, you see,

00:39.170 --> 00:43.440
there's only one electron
in a hydrogen atom.

00:45.210 --> 00:47.750
Best and brightest,
my sweet patootie.

00:47.750 --> 00:49.410
All right, let's begin.

00:49.410 --> 00:51.830
Show of hands,
who here is familiar

00:51.830 --> 00:54.490
with the concept
of topological insulators?

00:55.390 --> 00:56.990
Don't kid yourselves.

00:59.290 --> 01:01.960
I found another tweet from a
student at Sheldon's lecture.

01:01.960 --> 01:04.800
"Dr. Cooper has taken
a relatively boring subject

01:04.800 --> 01:08.300
"and managed to make it
completely insufferable.

01:08.300 --> 01:11.300
Plus, he looks
like a giant insect."

01:12.200 --> 01:13.500
Look. Listen to this one.

01:13.500 --> 01:17.110
"Does Einstein's theory
explain why time flies

01:17.110 --> 01:18.240
"when you're having fun,

01:18.240 --> 01:20.310
"but when you're listening
to Dr. Cooper,

01:20.310 --> 01:21.980
it falls out of the sky, dead?"

01:23.150 --> 01:24.480
Ooh, somebody took pictures

01:24.480 --> 01:27.350
and uploaded them
to their Flickr account.

01:27.350 --> 01:28.750
Wow.

01:28.750 --> 01:30.490
How do you get an
entire lecture hall

01:30.490 --> 01:32.820
to flip you off
at the same time?

01:32.820 --> 01:34.460
Apparently, if you're Sheldon,

01:34.460 --> 01:36.930
all you need
to do is turn your back.

01:36.930 --> 01:39.700
Hey, Leonard,
is your wi-fi down?

01:39.700 --> 01:40.660
I can't get on.

01:40.670 --> 01:42.130
Oh, Sheldon changed
the password.

01:42.130 --> 01:44.370
It's now
"Penny is a freeloader."

01:45.340 --> 01:46.740
No spaces.

01:46.740 --> 01:48.770
Thanks.
What are you guys doing?

01:48.770 --> 01:50.540
Sheldon gave a lecture
at the university tonight.

01:50.540 --> 01:51.810
We're reading
the reviews.

01:51.810 --> 01:53.140
Oh. How'd he do?

01:53.140 --> 01:55.280
Well, picture the Hindenburg
meets Chernobyl

01:55.280 --> 01:57.850
meets Three Mile Island
meets <i>Tron 2.</i>

01:57.850 --> 02:00.070
That bad, huh?

02:00.070 --> 02:02.400
Read this woman's tweet.

02:02.400 --> 02:04.820
"Listening to Dr. Cooper

02:04.820 --> 02:07.320
has made me want to start
cutting myself again""

02:07.330 --> 02:09.030
Yeah.

02:10.560 --> 02:13.100
Good evening,
Leonard, Howard, Raj,

02:13.100 --> 02:15.400
